[normal]D[bold]etention [bold]and legal aid[bold] [bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Sudarshan[bold]’s[bold] [bold]c[bold]ase [bold]&#xa0;[bold]Sudarshan
[normal], a 57 year old Pakistani National, 
[normal]was detained by the 
[normal]UK
[normal] Border Agency
[normal] [bold]during an immigration raid in 2007. She
[normal] spent three years in immigration detention during which
[normal] 
[normal]she was 
[normal]ill treated and 
[normal]denied access to urgent medical treatment. 
[normal]She states that 
[normal]immigration officials
[normal] often
[normal] shouted at her and treated her like an 
[normal]‘
[normal]animal
[normal]’ causing her to
[normal] suffe
[normal]r
[normal] a complete mental 
[normal]health breakdown. With the assistance of immigration lawyers, she was
[normal] eventually
[normal] able to leave the detention centre and was granted refugee status for five years. She 
[normal]brought a claim
[normal] 
[normal]against the UK
[normal]BA
[normal] for 
[normal]unlawful detention and 
[normal]ill-treatment experienced dur
[normal]ing detention. 
[normal]Her claim was settled in September 201 and she was awarded 42,500 in damages. 
[normal]Her 
[normal]detention 
[normal]and ill 
[normal]- 
[normal]treatment has had a 
[normal]permanent impact on her 
[normal]mental 
[normal]health
[normal]. She is suffering from chronic post - traumatic stress disorder.
